Regal International Inc said it proposedto submit a plan of reorganization with the U.S. BankruptcyCourt under which it will acquire Bell Petroleum Services INc'sby paying out all of its creditors and issue one share for eachshares of Bell's stock.    This proposal has been amended from a previously rejectedoffer of .50 Regal share for each Bell share.    Regal said its will pursue the acquisition without thesupport of Bell's management.    Bell Petroleum filed its Chapter 11 petition in November1986 and has not, as yet, filed a plan of reorganization buthas only sought an order extending the exclusive order,according to Regal.    Bell Petroleum President Ed Runyan said the company isevaluating Regal's latest offer and evaluating otheralternatives.    Runyan said Bell is meeting tomorrow with another potentialsuitor.    Reuter&#3;